-- China shares end week down on property, Great Wall sell-off
-- By Natalie Thomas
-- Fri May 09, 2014 03:09AM EDT
-- None



BEIJING, May 9 (Reuters) - China shares closed down on Friday on falling property stocks and a sell-off in Great Wall Motor shares, leaving the two main indexes in negative territory for the fourth straight week.

The Shanghai Composite Index <.SSEC> ended down 0.2 percent at 2,011.13 points. The CSI300 <.CSI300> of the leading Shanghai and Shenzhen A-share listings declined 0.1 percent. The CSI300 was down 1.1  percent on the week, while the Shanghai Composite lost 0.7 percent.  Property stocks continued to tumble, with the CSI real estate sub-index <.CSICMREI> losing another 1.5 percent, leaving overall losses for the week at 4.7 percent as indications of an imminent slowdown in the sector continue to build.